(15, 'EC changes picture format ahead of UP polls', ' Ahead of the Uttar Pradesh assembly polls  the Election Commission of India has made pasting of photographs on nomination papers of candidates mandatory  an official said on Saturday.. LUCKNOW: Putting an end to speculation about a "Maha-gathbandhan" in the Uttar Pradesh Assembly election  Samajwadi Party supremo Mulayam Singh Yadav Thursday ruled out forming alliance with any party and said "There may be only merger"..', ''),
(16, 'JNU missing student"s case transferred to Crime Branch', ' Delhi police has transferred the case of the missing Jawaharlal Nehru University student Najeeb Ahmed to its crime branch  an official said.. "The accused  identified as Pushpendra Patel  posted as maths teacher at Government Higher Secondary School  Naharpali under Bhupdeopur police station limits  was held last night based on the complaint of the students" relatives " Raigarh Additional Superintendent of Police UBS Chauhan said..', ''),
(17, 'Kejriwal demands rollback of demonetisation', ' Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal on Saturday demanded rollback of the government"s decision to demonetise Rs 500 and Rs 1 000 currency notes  saying that the economy will collapse in the coming days if the decision was not withdrawn.NEW DELHI: Dubbing the demonetisation of high currency notes as a"huge scam"  Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal Saturday alleged BJP had told all its "friends" about the move much before Prime Minister Narendra Modi"s announcement and demanded its immediate roll back.. The former Union Minister further said that 86 per cent of the total value of currency notes in circulation was in the denomination of Rs 500 or Rs 1 000.The government has announced its decision to withdraw Rs 500 and Rs 1 000 notes..', ''),
(18, 'Clear Saturday morning in Delhi', ' It was a clear Saturday morning here with shallow fog. The minimum temperature recorded was at 12.1 degrees Celsius, one below the season"s average.', ''),
(19, 'Rumour of salt shortage triggers panic in UP, one dead', ' Rumours of no salt stocks in Uttar Pradesh triggered a major law and order situation, leading to the death of a woman in Kanpur, police said on Saturday.', ''),
